Version 3.13.2, 2026-04-24

  Platform expansion and production hardening

New services:
- Add pi-custom-captive submodule — self-service TOTP captive portal
  with one-shot user enrolment and admin 2FA challenge-response flow.
  Stateless (no DB, no service account), every PI call runs on the
  actor's own JWT.
- Add centralized rsyslog container (fullstack profile) — receives
  syslog UDP/514 from privacyIDEA, FreeRADIUS, VPN Pooler and Captive
  Portal; writes per-service log files to the rsyslog_logs volume.

Syslog and logging:
- Add remote syslog forwarding to privacyIDEA via PI_SYSLOG_* env vars.
  entrypoint.py dynamically injects SysLogHandler into logging.cfg at
  startup.
- Add remote syslog forwarding to rlm_python3 FreeRADIUS plugin
  (RADIUS_SYSLOG_* env vars) with DEBUG full-packet dumps, secret
  redaction and accounting handler.
- Add remote syslog forwarding to pi-vpn-pooler and pi-custom-captive
  Django apps (SYSLOG_* env vars) with DEBUG HTTP request/response
  logging and secret redaction.

Environment and configuration:
- Split monolithic application-prod.env / application-dev.env into
  per-service env files under environment/{prod,dev}/ (compose.env,
  db.env, privacyidea.env, freeradius.env, vpn_pooler.env, captive.env).
  Each file uses actual variable names the app expects — no more
  prefix-stripping in docker-compose.yaml.
- Add make secrets target to auto-generate and write random secrets
  into per-service env files (PI_SECRET, PI_PEPPER, PI_ADMIN_PASS,
  PI_ENCKEY, DB_PASSWORD, Django secret keys for VPN Pooler and
  Captive Portal).
- Add make superadmin-policy target to import superadmin policy JSON
  into a running privacyIDEA instance (admin API permissions, WebUI
  dashboard, user self-service TOTP enrollment).
- Add SESSION_COOKIE_AGE support for VPN Pooler and Captive Portal
  with JWT exp-based session pinning.

Build and deployment:
- Expand build-images.sh with selective build/export by short names,
  help command, and archive bundling (repo + Docker images in one
  .tar.gz for offline deployment).
- Add setup-service.sh and templates/privacyidea-docker.service for
  systemd service installation (non-root, auto-start on boot).
- Add make install-service / make uninstall-service targets.
- Change NGINX_TLS_CERT_PATH / NGINX_TLS_KEY_PATH to control the
  host-side bind mount source for production TLS certificates.

Dev environment:
- Add docker-compose.dev.yaml override for subproject hot-reload:
  bind-mounts pi-vpn-pooler and pi-custom-captive source with gunicorn
  --reload, bind-mounts privacyidea_radius.py into freeradius.
- Add PI_SEED_RESOLVERS for dev-only idempotent resolver/realm import
  on first boot.
- Add /etc/hosts read-only bind mount to all prod stack services.

Submodules:
- Register pi-custom-captive, pi-vpn-pooler and rlm_python3 in
  .gitmodules with branch tracking.
- VPN Pooler DB init script removed — pooler is now fully stateless
  (YAML-backed pool storage, no database).

Documentation:
- Major README.md restructuring with full coverage of new services,
  environment variables, systemd deployment, offline deployment and
  syslog configuration.
- Add README.ru.md translations for all projects (privacyidea-docker,
  pi-custom-captive, pi-vpn-pooler, rlm_python3, design_handoff).
- Add EN/RU cross-links to all README files.

Bug fixes:
- Fix captive portal and VPN Pooler static files 404 in prod: moved
  collectstatic from Dockerfile build-time to container startup.
- Fix instantiate() crash in rlm_python3 when FreeRADIUS passes None
  config.
- Change privacyIDEA source to upstream privacyidea/privacyidea.

Version 3.13.1, 2026-04-17

  Fork and restructure

- Migrate database backend from MariaDB to PostgreSQL 16
- Single PostgreSQL instance shared between privacyIDEA and VPN Pooler
- Replace gpappsoft/privacyidea-freeradius with locally built rlm_python3
  (FreeRADIUS Python plugin via git submodule)
- Add pi-vpn-pooler service (VPN IP pool manager, git submodule)
- All application images are now built locally (no prebuilt cloud images)
- Add build-images.sh script for build/export/import of all images
- Add build-all Makefile target
- Add vpn_pooler compose profile
- Add init-vpn-pooler-db.sh for automatic database initialization
- Update environment files for PostgreSQL (DB_API=postgresql+psycopg2)

